OL,3,CZambia running dry: What do rich
OL,4,Cnations owe countries on the climate
OL,5,Cfrontline?
OL,7,FOthers crowd into malls, where huge
OL,8,Fbackup generators keep the power on,
OL,9,Fgathering in cafes to plug their
OL,10,Flaptops in for work.
OL,12,FIn shopping centre corridors, any
OL,13,Fpower socket on the wall has someone's
OL,14,Fmobile phone plugged in for charging.
OL,16,FEven the traffic lights are not always
OL,17,Fswitched on, leaving drivers to
OL,18,Fnavigate the roads without them.
OL,20,FThe cost is especially high for small
OL,21,Fbusinesses.
